342	/**
343	 * @brief An N-dimensional matrix supporting arbitrary (continuous) index ranges per dimension.
344	 * 
345	 * Examples:
346	 * 
347	 *       //A 2-dimensional matrix with indices [0..4][0..9]
348	 *       NdMatrix<int,2> m1({5,10});
